Per-element native HUD visibility gating (companion "Vanilla HUD Elements" options).

Each native top-screen HUD element (health/magicka/fatigue bars, equipped weapon+spell,
minimap, active effects, sneak indicator, crosshair, target/enemy health bar) is gated on
a companion Boolean, pushed from Kotlin into androidmain.cpp atomics and read here via
companionHud*(). ANDing the native-intended visibility with the companion flag in each
HUD-level setter is the independent chokepoint; a re-apply in HUD::onFrame (using the
cached native intent) makes toggles take effect live, since weapon/sneak are not re-applied
by updateVisible(). The crosshair setter is driven every frame from the camera, so it needs
no onFrame re-apply. The enemy health bar has no visibility setter (it is self-managed via
setEnemy() + an onFrame fade timer), so it is gated by an early return in setEnemy() (which
also skips the coupled mWeaponSpellBox -20px shift) plus an onFrame re-apply that force-
hides a still-visible bar and restores the +20px shift (mirroring the vanilla timeout hide)
for instant live toggling. All #ifdef __ANDROID__ so desktop is unchanged.

